<Author>Fjellvandrere
<Content>Excellent taste of the 80's We stayed at Casa Blanca for a total of 5 nights during our trip to Mexico. First for two nights on arrival in Mexico (booked in advance) and the 3 nights at the end of the trip (booked after the first two nights due to high satisfaction).Casa Blanca hotel is very clean and has good sized rooms in 80's colour and style (mint green, purple and pink). The beds are fairly comfortable and the rooms come with cable TV, nice bathroom and safe. We got a room on the 11th floor during our 1st stay with great views of the western part of the city and the Plaza de la Republica. On the second stay we had a room on the 8th floor with an equally good view. Views are also excellent from the rooftop terrace with swimming pool (heated) and bar.Most of the staff is extremely friendly at Casa Blanca. Especially the breakfast waiters who adds to the already splendid breakfast buffet. Also the porters, receptionists and cleaners are very friendly. Only the bar staff could put on more of a smile, even though they are cordial and friendly enough.We recommend this hotel which provides excellent value for money (we paid USD 93,00 per night including taxes and breakfast). 
