<Author>Dolphin76
<Content>Uninspiring I stayed at this hotel for 3 nights before starting my tour of Mexico. I found this hotel completely uninspiring. It's a very old-fashioned hotel, certainly in need of refurbishment. Especially corridors and rooms are pretty ugly and feature a smelly, old carpet. Rooms are small and painted of a ridicolous pink colours. Most of them have a view on a even more ugly inside courtyard. On the good side, I found breakfast to be pretty good in terms of quality and varierty of products served. I used their internet service and I found it very quick, efficient and not expensive at all. Another good point is the hotel location: right in the centre of the city, at walking distance from zocalo and zona rosa. Nontheless I would not stay at this hotel again. There was just no atmosphere. I'm sure Mexico City has got plenty of more modern and more inspiring places to stay. 
